>> title: Mediterranean Turkey Meatball Bowls
>> servings: 4
>> prep time: 20 minutes
>> cook time: 25 minutes

@{For tzatziki:}1. Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).

@{For tzatziki:}2. In a large bowl, combine ground @turkey{1.5%lbs}, @whole wheat breadcrumbs{0.5%cup}, @egg{1%large}, @garlic{2%cloves}, @oregano{1%tsp}, @parsley{2%tbsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @black pepper{0.5%tsp}. Mix gently until just combined.

@{For tzatziki:}3. Form into 20-24 meatballs, about 1.5 inches each.

@{For tzatziki:}4. Place meatballs on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon @extra virgin olive oil{3%tbsp}.

@{For tzatziki:}5. On a separate baking sheet, toss @zucchini{2%medium} and @bell peppers{2} with remaining @extra virgin olive oil{3%tbsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @black pepper{0.5%tsp}.

@{For tzatziki:}6. Bake both sheets for 20-25 minutes until meatballs are cooked through and vegetables are tender.

@{For tzatziki:}7. Meanwhile, prepare @brown rice or quinoa{2%cups} according to package directions.

@{For tzatziki:}8. For tzatziki: Mix @plain Greek yogurt{1%cup}, @cucumber{0.5}, @garlic{2%cloves}, @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, and @dill{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{1%tsp}.

@{For tzatziki:}9. Serve meatballs over rice/@brown rice or quinoa{2%cups} with roasted vegetables and tzatziki on the side.

-- Category: Mediterranean
-- Cholesterol benefits: Lean turkey instead of beef reduces saturated fat. Whole grains provide fiber. Olive oil and vegetables add heart-healthy nutrients. The tzatziki is a great way to get kids to eat their vegetables - they love dipping!
